  <h3>Microbial Risk</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>NSF and Nature studies (2015‚Äì2025) confirm: <strong>over 50% of machines</strong> harbor mold, yeast, or bacteria.</li>
    <li>Steam wands and group heads are hotspots for pathogens (including E. coli and Salmonella in rare cases).</li>
    <li>One study identified up to <strong>67 bacterial strains</strong> in a single machine.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Cost of Neglect</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Maintenance accounts for <strong>15‚Äì20% of total cost of ownership</strong> (Fortune Business Insights).</li>
    <li>Poor cleaning causes <strong>1‚Äì3 days of downtime per month</strong> in small caf√©s.</li>
    <li>Estimated revenue loss: <strong>$500‚Äì$2,000+/month</strong> (Mordor Intelligence, 2026).</li>
  </ul>

