  <h3>Operational Challenges</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Labor shortages ‚Üí less frequent cleaning.</li>
    <li>EU Right-to-Repair Directive (2024‚Äì2026) increases service costs.</li>
    <li>Fluctuating bean prices and tariffs squeeze margins ‚Üí maintenance deprioritized.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Recommendations</h2>

  <h3>Daily / Weekly</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Backflush group heads</li>
    <li>Purge and wipe steam wands after each use</li>
    <li>Empty and rinse drip trays & grounds bins</li>
    <li>Discard standing water in reservoirs</li>
  </ul>
  <p>‚Üí Reduces microbial load by 70‚Äì80%.</p>

  <h3>Monthly / Quarterly</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Full descaling with food-safe acid</li>
    <li>Replace gaskets, shower screens, and seals</li>
    <li>Schedule professional service ($200‚Äì$500/visit in the U.S.)</li>
  </ul>
  <p>‚Üí Prevents 50% of avoidable downtime.</p>

  <blockquote>
    ‚ÄúHow do your guests know you cleaned the machine? Trust isn‚Äôt enough ‚Äî proof is.‚Äù
  </blockquote>

  <h3>Tooling for Compliance</h3>
  <p>Studies on preventive maintenance show that <strong>visible tracking increases compliance by 40‚Äì60%</strong>. Digital logs, QR codes, and public status pages close the ‚Äútrust gap‚Äù between staff action and customer perception.</p>

